description.value: If Naiethar takes radiant damage, regeneration doesn't function until the end of her next turn.

Necrotic

Aura 3

Any creature without forest walk takes 5 necrotic damage each time it moves or is pushed, pulled, or slid into a square within the aura.

Basic Attack

At-Will ✦ Necrotic

Standard

+28 vs AC; 2d8+5 damage, and ongoing 5 necrotic (save ends).

Basic Attack

At-Will ✦ Necrotic

Standard

Ranged 10

+27 vs Reflex; 3d6+5 damage per attack, and the target is slid 4 squares. At the end of the slide, the target takes 10 ongoing necrotic damage and is restrained (save ends both)..

Basic Attack

At-Will ✦ Psychic

Minor 1/Round, At-Will

Close burst 3

Targets one creature restrained by branch blast; +27 vs Will; 1d6+3 damage plus 2d8 psychic damage, and the target is dazed (save ends); First Failed Saving Throw: 2d8 psychic damage; Second Failed Saving Throw: target is instead stunned (save ends).

Encounter ✦ Psychic

Standard

Close burst 5

+27 vs Will; 4d12+8 psychic damage, and the target is pushed 5 squares and falls prone.

Poison

Standard, Recharges When First Bloodied

Area burst 3 within 10

Trigger: When first bloodied

+27 vs Fortitude; 4d8+9 poison damage, and the target is slowed (save ends).

At-Will ✦ Illusion

Minor

Naiethar can disguise herself to appear as any Medium humanoid, usually a beautiful elf or eladrin. A successful Insight check (opposed by her Bluff check) pierces the disguise.

At-Will ✦ Necrotic, Teleportation

Move

Naiethar teleports up to 8 squares if she begins and ends the move adjacent to a tree, a treant, or a plant of Large size or larger. When she teleports in this manner, she deals 10 necrotic damage to all nonplant creatures adjacent to her at the end of the teleport.

When Naiethar is reduced to 0 hit points, she dissipates into a spray of dead leaves but is not truly destroyed. She reappears in 1d10 days within 1 square of her phylactery tree, unless the phylactery tree is also destroyed.
